@NODE "The Author"
@REM 12 Oct 1995 mikew
@{b}The Author@{ub}

    I'm an Amiga programmer since 1987 and I've been doing it as my source of
    income since 1990 (It's great to get paid for having fun). I was a commercial
    Amiga Developer until CBM went out of business. I'm mostly into writing medical
    software for the Amiga. I'm the author of the TeleRadiology software that
    was distributed through National Diagnostic Imaging, Inc. (There @{i}are@{ui} some
    TeleRadiology units out there in hospitals and doctor's homes that are based
    upon an Amiga 3000 and the A2410 Display Card!)

    I also write some software for OS/2 (the next best thing).

